Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to position nearest flame and preheat broiler to high. Line a #baking sheet{} with foil. Prick @Russet Potato{2} all over with a fork, then rub with a drizzle of @olive oil{}. Season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place in a large #bowl{}. Microwave on high for ~{5%minutes}.

Flip potatoes over with #tongs{} and microwave until tender, ~{5-7%minutes} more. Set aside to cool. Meanwhile, trim @Scallions{2}. Mince white parts until you have 1 TBSP; thinly slice the rest. Remove any large stems from @Parsley{1/2%ounce}, then finely chop. Zest 1 tsp zest from @Lemon{1}, then halve. Squeeze 1 TBSP juice into a small bowl. Finely mince @Garlic{2%cloves}.

In a small bowl, mix @olive oil{3%tablespoon}, minced scallion whites, parsley, garlic (to taste—start with half and add more from there), lemon juice, half the lemon zest, and a pinch of @Chili Flakes{1%teaspoon}. Season with salt and more chili flakes to taste. Place @Cream Cheese{4%tablespoon} and @Butter{1%tablespoon} in a medium bowl. Microwave until just softened, about ~{10%seconds}.

Halve potatoes lengthwise. Carefully scoop out insides, leaving about ¼-inch around the perimeter. Add insides to bowl with cream cheese, followed by @Sour Cream{6%tablespoon}, half the @Italian Cheese Blend{1%cup}, remaining scallions, and a large pinch of salt and pepper. Mash until mostly smooth with a #potato masher{}. Stuff skins with potato mixture. Place on lined baking sheet. Sprinkle with remaining Italian cheese and set aside.

Heat a drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{2%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Dry @Sirloin Steak{24%ounce} with a #paper towel{}; season with salt and pepper. Cook in pan until done, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #cutting board{}. Wipe pan, heat a drizzle of oil in it over medium-high heat, and add @Sugar Snap Peas{12%ounce}, 2 TBSP water, and salt and pepper. Cook until tender, ~{2-3%minutes}. Take off heat and stir in @Dijon Mustard{2%teaspoon}, rest of zest, @Butter{1%tablespoon}, salt, and pepper.

Broil potatoes until cheese melts and begins to brown, about ~{3%minutes}. Divide between plates and sprinkle each with a pinch of @Paprika{1%teaspoon}. Slice steak against grain, then add to plates. Spoon garlic sauce over steak. Drain @Capers{1%ounce} and scatter over steak (skip this for picky eaters). Serve with snap peas to the side.

> This recipe has "Sunday dinner" written all over it: a special meal worth sharing with family, with extra attention to every detail. The sirloin steaks get their own special sauce in the form of a flavorful mix of garlic and herbs with a few capers for garnish. The snap peas, too, are anything but plain—they have a tangy mustard coating. Although the real showstopper might be the stuffed potato skins, which are irresistibly creamy thanks to a nice helping of cheese.